<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Buss2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Buss,</orth> vb., to kiss: <cit><quote>and b. thee as thy wife,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 3.4.35" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 4, 35</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>yond towers whose wanton tops do b. the clouds,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 4.5.220" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. IV, 5, 220</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>thy knee --ing the stones,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 3.2.75" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 2, 75</bibl></cit> (cf. <emph>Ear-bussing</emph>).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>